Phillip Jamerson
CEO

 

Phillip graduated from Virginia Tech in 1982 with a Bachelor of Science degree in Building Construction. As the third generation of J.E. Jamerson & Sons, Phillip grew up as a member of his family business, providing him with a lifetime of knowledge of the construction industry. With over 30 years of construction experience, he started as a general laborer during the summers and steadily progressed to foreman, superintendent, project manager and project executive. Phillip has been associated with some of the industry’s largest jobs. At Jamerson-Lewis, Phillip will oversee construction as Chief Operating Officer. Phillip Jamerson is now 1 of 4 owners of Jamerson Lewis Construction Inc. 







Would you like to work with us?
You can email us or use our contact page. We'd love to talk with you about your next project.






" As a leader in the construction industry, Jamerson-Lewis is known for their highly skilled workforce. We have always found their workmanship to be above industry standards. Their willingness to go the extra mile has always produced a quality and very reliable product.....Southern Air, Inc regards Jamerson-Lewis as one of the best general contractors in the Southeast".Ronald G. Kidd, Jr. President Southern Air, Inc."Our Department has been very pleased with the professional performance of Jamerson-Lewis Construction, Inc. during the completion of the alterations and additions to Midlothian High School....The project design was phased, unique and complex. The time for completion was compressed. The project team was proactive in their scheduling and phase completions. The owner and the users were amazed with the smooth transition into these new and renovated spaces. Jamerson-Lewis met every time sensitive issue and moved to the completion dates with ease. I would highly recommend this company to any other architect, engineer or owner."Everett A. Minton, Jr.Chesterfield County Public SchoolsI have worked with William Cook of Jamerson Lewis Construction, Inc. on several construction projects since 2008 where I served as the Project Architect. Throughout the time I’ve known him, he has shown me time and again that he has excellent project management skills (very thorough, a team player and has a positive attitude). In summary, due to his ability to coordinate closely and effectively with the owner, architect, and subcontractors I highly recommend William as a Project Manager for your projects.

Alan Burchette, AIA Senior Associate
Dewberry Engineers Inc.

Architecture Department Manager"William Cook and I worked together on the Livestock Road Region 2000. Regional Landfill Facilities Project in 2011-2012.  The project consisted of constructing a new Office Building, Maintenance Building, Scale House, Convenience Station and general site development.  William helped deliver this project on schedule while coordinating Jamerson Lewis' work with several other contractors working for Region 2000. William's professionalism, organization and commitment to meeting the project schedule were integral to the project's success.  As an Owner, I highly recommend William Cook as a Construction Project Manager."
Clarke W. Gibson, P.E.
Director
