 “…The goal of Jamerson-Lewis always seems to be making sure the client is satisfied. We have worked with other contractors with goals of making a profit over making happy customers. This makes working with Jamerson-Lewis a positive experience, not just a job.”
Kim BassProject ManagerLongwood University“Jamerson-Lewis Construction, Inc. completed a major restoration and rehabilitation project at the Old Court House in 2005. The project required that the historic fabric and character of the 1855 building be restored to high standards while adding systems to protect the building and artifacts preserved here. We are very pleased with the end result and receive many compliments from our visitors who often tell us they love the restored building environment as well as the exhibits.”
Douglas K. HarveyMuseum DirectorThe Lynchburg Museum System“Luck is the random result of circumstances and situations void of directed influences. Luck had nothing to do with our accomplishment. It is the result of highly skilled and dedicated professionals working together safely to an expected and defined goal. Without these men and women and their amazing contributions to this endeavor, none of this would be possible.”
John W. Compher, PE, CPEManager, Industrial EngineeringBabcock & Wilcox Nuclear Operations Group“I recommend Jamerson-Lewis Construction as a highly motivated and experienced builder in the design/build arena. Their abilities were irreplaceable in our success in this building endeavor. We would not hesitate to contract with them again in the future.”
Douglas A. CooperPresidentLiberty Construction Services, Inc.“The recent renovation and build out of additional space done by your company through our property manager was excellent. We appreciated the professionalism of your people and in particular the fine communication system used by your company to assure us along the way that the job met our specifications.”
Michael E. Watson & R. Gregory Porter, IIIInvestment CounselsFlippin, Bruce & Porter, Inc.“…What a great group of people you have assembled. From Mrs. Brooks [C.L. Lewis & Company secretary for 45 years], whose dedication and loyalty are inspirational, to a group of Superintendents that I am sure your competitors envy, you have something special. Good people are the difference!”
John M. Jordan, IIIPresidentHawkins-Graves, Inc.“I would like to express my appreciation to you and your staff on behalf of the City of Lynchburg for a job well done. … The level of pride shown by your employees in their work is a real testament to their commitment to provide quality services. … I am pleased to say this has been a wonderful experience for all of us and I highly recommend Jamerson-Lewis Construction, Inc. to others in need of a quality job accomplished.”
D’Anna Conner, PEPrincipal EngineerCity of Lynchburg’s Monument Terrace“Your ability to actually estimate the construction project costs, to orchestrate the construction timelines and your willingness to work with us to minimize the number of change orders enabled us to complete a successful project that was under budget and on time… Again, thank you for your professionalism, attention to construction detail and to the project’s bottom line.”
W. J. ThomasExecutive DirectorValley Community Services Board“Your creativity and goodwill during the negotiating phase was most welcomed, and your leadership, fairness and judgment on the jobsite made the construction process enjoyable from beginning to end. Thanks, too, for your determined effort at completing the last few items of work, and insuring the Owner’s long-term satisfaction.”
Ken ThackerAssociate PrincipalVMDO Architects“From line carpenter to the foreman to the subcontractors, everyone was skilled and professional, and the job was ably managed from your office… Regular site meetings and your personal involvement assured that the project stayed on schedule, and I always felt I was treated fairly in change order negotiations.”
George KriegerExecutive DirectorNelson County Community Development Foundation“From my viewpoint, the team at Jamerson-Lewis Construction uniquely possesses the skill set and initiative to meet the challenges of modern construction. Whether restoring an 1855 courthouse or building the City of Lynchburg’s first LEED building, Jamerson-Lewis Construction delivers repeat performances of ‘a job well done.’”
Amanda G. Adams, LEED AP (BD+C)Associate AIACJMW Architecture“I appreciate their strong leadership and customer service. Their project managers and superintendents are well-versed and experienced with the complexities of healthcare renovation work such as interim life safety measures, infection control measures, medical gas systems, fire safety systems, fire-stopping, emergency power, and complex phasing. I have a high regard for Jamerson-Lewis Construction, Inc…”
Joe Archambeault, PE, CHFMManaging Director of FacilitiesCentra Health, Inc.“…I am deeply indebted to all who worked in planning the science building at Sweet Briar. It is a magnificent, functional laboratory. Last but not least, it all culminated in the joyful, happy celebration of dedication in April. It has convinced me that wherever a group joins together to work a miracle it will succeed. You all did work a miracle! Thanks and thanks!”
Connie M. Guion, M.D.Sweet Briar College Professor 1908-1913In a letter to C.L. Lewis dated June 7, 1966 








